The Federal Reserve Bank of San Francisco, Los Angeles Branch is the Southern California branch of the Federal Reserve Bank of San Francisco located on West Olympic Boulevard and South Olive, in southern Downtown Los Angeles. It is within the Twelfth Federal Reserve District.


== Buildings ==
The original 1929 building was designed by John and Donald Parkinson in a Classical Moderne style with elements of zigzag moderne.
